Re: Difference between ことになったand ことになっている？
by MizukoHito » Tue 08.30.2011 4:54 pm Yeah, I think you two are right about ことになっている meaning an ongoing or continuous process. It kind of makes sense, since my book also says that it's used when talking about traditions and common practices, etc.Like:日本では、家に入る時、くつをぬぐことになっています。
MizukoHito
