Re: Difference between ことになったand ことになっている？
by squarezebra » Wed 08.31.2011 5:56 pm If its helpful, I think of ことになっている as making something become 'customary'. As a result of it being decided in the past (ことになった）it has now become customary (ことになっている)
Spend less time thinking, and more time doing. squarezebra
